AB  - In January 2008, the City Council of San Sebastian adopted the Action Plan on Climate Change (APCC), after a long process of public participation and deliberation. The strategic plan and urban plan were used to support the development of the community's APCC, with inter-departmental cooperation leading to a coherent strategy. Furthermore, building on the results of the inclusive process - the Local Agenda 21 (LA21) approach the Plan was developed based on four strategic themes, with more than 220 actions implemented. An economic study was carried out to analyse the cost of the Local Action Plan, and research was conducted to develop future reduction scenarios, to consider the potential impact of different climate protection actions. The integration of the Local Agenda 21 process and climate protection strategies is regarded as one of the main success factors, and forms the foundation of sustainability policy-making in San Sebastian.
