AB  - The U.S. Army Corps of Engineers has been involved in shore protection studies since 1930, and in construction of hurricane protection and erosion control projects since shortly after World War II. Beach nourishment projects have proven especially popular with local interests. Budgetary constraints, however, have curtailed the Corps' ability to enter into commitments for new projects that could require periodic nourishment for as long as 50 years. With changes in the cost sharing formula between the Federal government and local sponsors, however, it may be possible once again to enter into commitments for new project construction. These changes are still pending with the Administration and Congress.
