AB  - This paper presents the outline of the study carried out by a Japanese committee on the impacts of and response options to the anticipated sea level rise and climate change induced by global warming. Various phases of the impacts as well as a structure of impacts propagation are listed focusing on ports and developed coasts. In addition, a systematic approach is developed to estimate the cost of protection by raising structures as a response option. It is shown that the cost can reach as much as 92 billion $ only to protect the ports, harbors, and their neighboring areas along the Japanese coast.
